# Git workflow

Every change follows this loop — do not skip steps.

1. **Branch** — create a new branch from `main` before editing (`cursor/…` or `feat/TW-NNN-slug` for task work). At session start: `git fetch origin && git checkout main && git pull --ff-only`.
2. **Commit & draft PR** — after each commit, run `pnpm check` (and `pnpm run work check` when touching `work/`), then `git push -u origin HEAD` (first push) or `git push`. On the first push, open a draft PR with `gh pr create --draft`. **Always open or update a draft PR** — never push commits without syncing them to GitHub. Task stays `status: active` while the PR is draft. Do not use `/review-bugbot` or local Bugbot.
3. **Finish implementation** — tick acceptance criteria, append to the task `## Log`, fill `pr` in frontmatter once the draft PR exists.
4. **Mark ready** — when implementation is complete, publish the PR: `gh pr ready`. Set task `status: review`. Put `Closes TW-NNN` in the PR body.
5. **Review & fix loop** — wait for GitHub PR review comments and CI; poll with `gh pr view --comments` and `gh pr checks` if needed. Address valid findings with commit + push; repeat until blocking comments are resolved and CI passes. If more implementation is needed, mark draft again with `gh pr ready --undo` and return to step 2.
6. **Merge & done** — **squash-merge** with `gh pr merge --squash` (or GitHub UI / merge queue), then `git checkout main && git pull --ff-only`. Set task `status: done` and `completed`. Work is complete only after merge.

Never commit directly to `main`. Never merge while the PR is still draft or before review and CI are clean on the published diff.
